The paper focuses on large-scale scene recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a multi-resolution CNN architecture and knowledge guided disambiguation techniques, which involve machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) concepts. Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on three large-scale image datasets, which includes multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) aspects.
